quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  30,11,God bringth forth the creation - then causeth it to return again - then to Him shall ye come back
  30,12,"And on the day when the hour shall arrive, the guilty shall be struck dumb for despair"
  30,13,"And they shall have no intercessors from among the gods whom they have joined with God, and they shall deny the gods they joined with Him"
  30,14,"And on that day when the Hour shall arrive, shall men be separated one from another"
  30,15,"And as for those who shall have believed and done the things that are right, they shall enjoy themselves in a flowery mead"
  30,16,"But as for those who shall not have believed, but treated our signs and the meeting of the next life as lies, they shall be given over to the torment"
  30,17,"Glorify God therefore when ye reach the evening, and when ye rise at morn"
  30,18,"And to Him be praise in the Heavens and on the Earth; and at twilight, and when ye rest at noon"
  30,19,"He bringeth forth the living out of the dead, and He bringeth forth the dead out of the living: and He quickeneth the earth when dead. Thus is it that ye too shall be brought forth"